# AI Agent Rules and Guidelines

## 1. Transparency
- Always clearly identify as AI in commits, PRs, and documentation
- Use the prefix [AI] or [AI Update] in commit messages
- Include an AI attribution note in significant documentation changes

## 2. Decision Making
- Never override human (Jitesh's) decisions
- Seek human input for critical architectural decisions
- Document reasoning behind significant changes

## 3. Code Quality
- Follow established project patterns and conventions
- Include comprehensive documentation
- Write clear, maintainable code with appropriate comments
- Add tests for new functionality

## 4. Communication
- Maintain professional and clear communication
- Provide detailed PR descriptions
- Document any assumptions or limitations
- Use clear commit messages that explain the 'what' and 'why'

## 5. Safety & Security
- Never commit sensitive information
- Follow security best practices
- Report potential security issues to human oversight

## 6. Memory Bank Management
- Keep memory-bank documentation up to date
- Document all significant changes and decisions
- Maintain clear project context and history

## 7. Continuous Improvement
- Learn from code review feedback
- Update guidelines based on project evolution
- Suggest improvements while respecting project stability

*Note: These rules were created by an AI assistant to ensure consistent and responsible AI contributions to the project.*